  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Fisher &amp; Paykel in LA — DishDrawer specialty service</h2>
    <p>Fisher &amp; Paykel's DishDrawer has been the brand's flagship dishwasher product since the 1990s, representing a genuinely distinctive take on residential dishwashing architecture. Instead of the industry-standard single-door front-loading design, DishDrawer uses one or two drawer compartments that slide out like kitchen drawers. Each drawer operates independently — its own wash pump, drain pump, heating element, control logic — so on a Double DishDrawer you can run the top drawer on Delicate wash for glassware while the bottom drawer runs Heavy on dinner plates, all simultaneously.</p>
    <p>LA DishDrawer installed base concentrates in four distinct kitchen segments. Compact urban apartments and condos (WeHo, Koreatown, Hollywood, Downtown LA, Silver Lake) where Single DishDrawer solves the full-size-dishwasher-won't-fit problem. Open-plan custom kitchens (Hollywood Hills, Pacific Palisades, Encino, Calabasas) where the drawer aesthetic matches island-kitchen architecture. Beverage-prep and secondary kitchens in larger premium households (Beverly Hills, Brentwood, Hidden Hills) where a glassware-dedicated DishDrawer lives near the bar. Accessibility-focused installs where the drawer form factor is easier to use than reaching into a low-door dishwasher. Haier's 2012 F&amp;P acquisition improved US parts distribution substantially.</p>
  </div></section>

