    <h2>DishDrawer vs standard dishwasher — honest trade-offs</h2>
    <p><b>DishDrawer advantages:</b> genuinely unique form factor, dual-zone simultaneous-cycle capability on Double DishDrawer, accessibility-friendly architecture, better fit for compact urban kitchens, design-aesthetic differentiation.</p>
    <p><b>DishDrawer trade-offs:</b> specialty parts with longer lead times than mainstream brands, smaller US installed base means fewer third-party parts options, repair economics on 15-plus-year units can push toward replacement faster than with mass-market dishwashers.</p>
    <p>For LA households where the drawer architecture specifically matters (compact kitchen, open-plan aesthetic, accessibility), DishDrawer delivers a product no mainstream brand offers. For households where drawer form factor isn't specifically required, standard front-door dishwashers from <a href="/brands/bosch-dishwasher-repair/">Bosch</a>, <a href="/brands/miele-dishwasher-repair/">Miele</a>, or mainstream brands offer simpler service economics.</p>
